I'll add both conditions to help identify both patterns.

```pine
//@version=5
strategy("Volume MA Pullback Strategy", overlay=true)

// Input parameters
len1 = input(12, "MA1 Length")
len2 = input(26, "MA2 Length")
len3 = input(50, "MA3 Length")
volSmoothLen = input(2, "Volume Smoothing Length")

// Calculate MAs
ma12 = ta.sma(close, len1)
ma26 = ta.sma(close, len2)
ma50 = ta.sma(close, len3)

// Volume analysis
volSMA = ta.sma(volume, volSmoothLen)
isVolHigh = volume > volSMA
isBearishCandle = close < open
isBullishCandle = close > open

// Detect two consecutive bearish bars with high volume
twoRedBarsHighVol = isBearishCandle and isBearishCandle[1] and isVolHigh and isVolHigh[1]

// Detect one bearish bar followed by one bullish bar with high volume
bullishReversal = isBearishCandle[1] and isBullishCandle and isVolHigh[1] and isVolHigh

// Pullback conditions
isPriceAboveMA50 = close > ma50
isMA12aboveMA26 = ma12 > ma26
isPullback = ta.crossover(close, ma12) and isPriceAboveMA50 and isMA12aboveMA26

// Entry conditions
longCondition = isPullback and bullishReversal and not twoRedBarsHighVol

// Plot moving averages
plot(ma12, "MA12", color=color.blue)
plot(ma26, "MA26", color=color.yellow)
plot(ma50, "MA50", color=color.red)

// Plot signals
plotshape(
    series=bullishReversal and isPullback,  
    title="Bullish Reversal", 
    style=shape.xcross,
    location=location.belowbar, 
    color=color.green, 
    size=size.normal
)

plotshape(
    series=twoRedBarsHighVol,  
    title="Two Red Bars Warning", 
    style=shape.xcross,
    location=location.belowbar, 
    color=color.red, 
    size=size.normal
)

plotchar(longCondition, "Long Signal", "â–²", location.belowbar, color.green, size=size.small)

// Strategy entry
if (longCondition)
    strategy.entry("Long", strategy.long)

// Exit when price closes below MA26
if (close < ma26)
    strategy.close("Long")
```

Key changes:
1. Kept the original `twoRedBarsHighVol` condition
2. Added the new `bullishReversal` condition
3. Now plotting both patterns:
   - Red X for two consecutive bearish bars with high volume
   - Green X for bearish-to-bullish reversal during pullback
4. Entry condition requires:
   - Pullback condition
   - Bullish reversal pattern
   - No two red bars warning

Let me know if you'd like any adjustments to either pattern or the visualizations!
